Body: I have same question but i have 10Mh/s. So could you plese tell me how can i set up solo mining?

Author: TRAID
Title: ‚úÖ [ANN] [NeoScrypt] [PoW+PoS+MN] ‚≠ê Traid.tv ‚≠ê The Future of Crypto Education ‚úÖ
Body: Here are the steps for solo mining:  1. Shut down your TRAID wallet  2. Open Traid folder  Windows: C:\Users\YOURUSER\AppData\Roaming\Traid Linux: ~/.Traid/ Mac: ~/Library/Application Support/Traid  3. Edit Traid.conf with the following:  rpcuser=random_name (one word) rpcpassword=random_password (one word) rpcallowip=127.0.0.1 rpcport=53568 server=1 listen=1 daemon=1  4. Open your miner config and set it to mine on this address:  http://127.0.0.1:53568 -u random_name -p random_password  HAPPY MINING!

Author: TRAID
Title: ‚úÖ [ANN] [NeoScrypt] [PoW+PoS+MN] ‚≠ê Traid.tv ‚≠ê The Future of Crypto Education ‚úÖ
Body: Please follow these steps:  1. Shut down your TRAID wallet  2. Open Traid folder  Windows: C:\Users\YOURUSER\AppData\Roaming\Traid Linux: ~/.Traid/ Mac: ~/Library/Application Support/Traid  3. Backup "wallet.dat" file and "backups" folder  4. Delete all contents from the Traid folder (except for "wallet.dat" file and "backups" folder that you previously backed up)  5. Download Traid blockchain data from the below link and extract it in Traid folder  https://github.com/TraidPlatform/traidcoin/releases/download/v2.0.0.0/Chaindata.zip  6. Start your wallet and let it sync  Hit @MJ on Discord if you still have issues. Thanks!

With all the unethical shillers and pump&dump schemes, beginners don't have anyone to turn to for the right guidance. We plan to change that.  Pro traders will also benefit from our education platform. It will allow them to share their knowledge and charge users for access to premium content, among other features.  To answer your question about other languages...yes, Traid platform will be multilingual.
